{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6ea5248-a2c0-44f2-becf-464d10e0bf54","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-file.dmp>\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the interactive session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the current thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**Using LLDB with SOS** (Linux):\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core <file.dmp>\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\nLoad the dump, then use `.loadby sos coreclr` and commands like `!pe`, `!clrstack`, `!threads`.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file interactively? If so, provide the path to your `.dmp` file and I can walk through the investigation with you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"67516dc9-d97c-4863-8b25-b7f7a25dc98c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze an existing dump, not collect one.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their .NET crash dump.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"5035:B7F6F:294447:337954:69F55589"},"id":"f5eeb201-bcaf-4a7e-8be0-4a3be15100f1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:38:30.038Z","parentId":"09595d5f-b581-4ec1-9037-683e89bfdc75"}
